# New City Generation Rules

Apply every rule below before considering a city entry complete.
These are derived from Valencia and Lisbon ‚Äî the reference standard.

---

## RULE 1 ‚Äî Checklist: every item must be connected

Every item in `actionChecklist` must have a `targetSection`.

Valid values: `"visa"` `"housing"` `"schools"` `"childcare"` `"healthcare"` `"residency"` `"banking"` `"safety"`

```json
// ‚ùå BAD ‚Äî dead item, no scroll target
{ "label": "Join the local Facebook group before arriving" }

// ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî connected to a real section
{ "label": "Join the local expat community ‚Äî ask landlord about TM30 filing", "targetSection": "residency" }
```

**Allowed exceptions:** at most 2 items per checklist may be general logistics (arrival timing, equipment, SIM). All others must have a target.

**Required order:** visa ‚Üí housing ‚Üí schools ‚Üí healthcare ‚Üí residency ‚Üí banking

---

## RULE 2 ‚Äî Content: no fluff, no risky claims

Every bullet must answer: **what is it / what should I do / why does it matter.**

```
// ‚ùå BAD ‚Äî vague, no action
"Healthcare is generally good in this city."

// ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî actionable, specific
"Register at your local clinic with your address certificate to activate public coverage ‚Äî required for your whole family."
```

**Do not paste Thailand-specific bureaucracy into non-Thailand cities.** If you are editing Japan, Singapore, Taiwan, Malaysia, Indonesia, etc., never reuse Bangkok-template phrases such as TM30 landlord filing, `imm.immigration.go.th` 90-day reporting, Thai Baht, Sukhumvit/Thonglor/Bang Na, Kasikorn/Bangkok Bank (unless the city is in Thailand), Bumrungrad/Samitivej as default hospitals, or Thai embassy / Thailand Elite URLs. Each country has its own immigration sites, address rules, and currency ‚Äî verify them for that `countrySlug` before saving.

**Do not use:**
- "world-class", "virtually zero", "best in the region", "top-tier"
- Exact government fee amounts (they change ‚Äî use "roughly" or "approximately")
- Exact processing times in days (use "typically 2‚Äì4 weeks")
- Hard claims about crime being zero or near-zero

**Do use:**
- "typically", "usually", "often", "many families", "roughly", "approximately"
- Named specifics: "Bangkok Bank and Kasikorn" not "local banks"
- One named hospital, one named bank per section where helpful ‚Äî not a comprehensive list
- For schools: NEVER name specific schools ‚Äî use category descriptions only (see Rule 5)

