## RULE 3 ‚Äî Local terms and acronyms: always explain inline

When a local term or acronym appears **anywhere** (checklist, section text, visa details, residency, banking, healthcare ‚Äî everywhere), define it in the same sentence. This applies both to local bureaucratic terms and to institution/programme name abbreviations.

```
// ‚ùå BAD ‚Äî acronym unexplained
"Apply for your Emirates ID within 30 days."

// ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî explained on first use
"Apply for your Emirates ID ‚Äî UAE's national identity card required for banking, healthcare, and school enrolment ‚Äî within 30 days."
```

```
// ‚ùå BAD ‚Äî institution abbreviation with no explanation
"Apply through the ICP portal."

// ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî expanded inline
"Apply through the ICP portal ‚Äî the ICP (Federal Authority for Identity, Citizenship, Customs and Port Security) is the UAE's federal body for all visa and identity services."
```

This applies to: Padr√≥n, NIE, NIF, TIE, Junta de Freguesia, Finan√ßas, AIMA, SNS, SIP, TM30, Emirates ID, KHDA, ADEK, ICP, DARI, FAB, ADCB, NOC, PRO, IPMI, moo ban, and any other local bureaucratic term or institution abbreviation.

