## RULE 5 ‚Äî Section structure: all required, correct format

Every city entry must include all of these sections.
`residency` and `banking` are **required objects**, not optional.
`housing` must have `searchPortalsIntro` and `searchPortals` populated.
`childcare` must use the three `*Items` arrays ‚Äî not the deprecated prose fields.
`healthcare` and `safety` must use `items[]` arrays ‚Äî not prose `summary` fields.

| Section | Required format |
|---|---|
| `actionChecklist` | 8‚Äì10 items, all targeted |
| `familyFit` | `bestFor` (4 items) + `watchOutFor` (4 items) |
| `visa` | 2‚Äì3 options with `anchor`, `detailTitle`, `details[]`, `officialLink` where stable ‚Äî set `"isVerified": true` on each link you confirm works |
| `residency` | **Required**. `title?`, `items[]` (4‚Äì5 bullets), `tip?` |
| `banking` | **Required**. `title?`, `items[]` (4‚Äì5 bullets), `tip?` |
| `housing` | **Required**: `searchPortalsIntro` (3 lines), `searchPortals[]`. Optional: `typicalPrices[]`, `whatYouNeedToRent[]` |
| `schools` | `summary`, `publicSystem`, `internationalOptions`, `languageNotes`, `tip`, `options[]` (2‚Äì4 entries) ‚Äî **never named schools** |
| `childcare` | **Required**: `daycareItems[]`, `nannyItems[]`, `whereToFindItems[]` ‚Äî no prose |
| `healthcare` | **Required**: `items[]` (5 bullets), `tip?` ‚Äî no prose `summary` |
| `safety` | **Required**: `items[]` (5 bullets), `score` (75‚Äì90) ‚Äî no prose `summary` |
| `cost` | `monthlyFamilyAllIn`, `rentRange`, `familyDinner`, `nannyRate` ‚Äî see Rule 6 |

**Do not leave any section as a placeholder string.** If data is unavailable, use honest approximations with "typically" ‚Äî never invent specific figures.

**Deprecated fields** ‚Äî do not use these in new city entries:
- `childcare.daycareNotes`, `nannyNotes`, `typicalCost`, `howFamiliesFindIt`
- `healthcare.summary` (use `items[]` instead)
- `safety.summary` (use `items[]` instead)
- `cost.childcare`, `cost.childcareType`, `cost.nannyHourly`

**Link verification ‚Äî required for every external URL:**
Every object with a `url` field must also have `"isVerified": true` (if you have confirmed it resolves) or `"isVerified": false` (if known broken). Never omit `isVerified` ‚Äî a missing value is treated as unverified and the link will not render as clickable.
```json
// ‚úÖ Required format for all link objects
{ "label": "Official site", "url": "https://example.gov", "isVerified": true }
```
This applies to: `communityLinks[]`, `housing.searchPortals[]`, `sources.*[]`, `visa.options[].officialLink`, `visa.options[].sections[].officialLink`.

**Schools use `options[]`, not `examples[]`** ‚Äî the renderer auto-generates a `SearchHint` from `option.type + city + country`. No URLs needed.

