## RULE 7 ‚Äî Visa: all options must be interactive

Every visa option must have:
- `anchor` ‚Äî a unique string like `"visa-dtv"`, `"visa-d8"`, `"visa-golden"`
- `detailTitle` ‚Äî descriptive heading for the detail panel
- `duration` ‚Äî **must answer ‚Äúhow long can I stay on this route?‚Äù** in plain language (e.g. ‚ÄúMany passports: about 90 days visa-free‚Äù, ‚ÄúTypically 1‚Äì2 years per Employment Pass issue‚Äù). Avoid useless placeholders like `Varies` without a typical range. If rules differ by nationality, say so and point to the official chart or a Google search link.
- `details[]` ‚Äî 4‚Äì6 flat bullet strings explaining how to apply

**Acronyms** (VoA, KITAS, EP, COE, ARC, etc.): expand on first use in that option's `type`, `description`, or `summary` ‚Äî e.g. `VoA (Visa on Arrival)`. For terms in `lib/visaGlossary.ts`, the UI can show a `?` hint ‚Äî add new keys there when you introduce country-specific jargon.

The `anchor` must also be registered in `components/VisaPathSelector.tsx` in the `ANCHOR_PATH` map.

Anchor ‚Üí path mapping:
- EU/EEA free movement ‚Üí `"eu"`
- Tourist / visa on arrival / short-stay ‚Üí `"tourist"`
- Remote work / digital nomad / long-stay / investment visa ‚Üí `"dnv"`

```typescript
// Add new anchors to ANCHOR_PATH in VisaPathSelector.tsx
"visa-my-new-anchor": "dnv",
```

