## Pre-flight checklist (run before saving a new city)

Before completing a new city entry, verify:

- [ ] Every checklist item has a valid `targetSection`
- [ ] No checklist item targets a section that doesn't exist in the data
- [ ] All `familyFit` arrays have exactly 4 items each
- [ ] All visa options have `anchor`, `detailTitle`, `duration` (plain-language stay length), and `details[]`
- [ ] New visa anchors are added to `VisaPathSelector.tsx`
- [ ] `housing` has all 4 blocks including `searchPortalsIntro` with 3 lines
- [ ] `childcare` uses 3 structured arrays ‚Äî no prose paragraphs
- [ ] `healthcare` and `safety` use `items[]` arrays ‚Äî no prose `summary`-only entries
- [ ] `residency` and `banking` are both present with `tip` fields
- [ ] `schools` has `options[]` with 2‚Äì4 category descriptions ‚Äî **no named schools, no `url` fields**
- [ ] `cost.monthlyFamilyAllIn` is set and matches FAQ #2; `rentRange` / `familyDinner` / `nannyRate` use **USD** and `~`; `nannyRate` is hourly
- [ ] If the destination is a searchable area tied to a hub we already cover, `relatedDestinationGuide` points at a real `countrySlug`/`citySlug` pair (or omit the field)
- [ ] Safety score is between 75 and 90
- [ ] No Facebook URLs anywhere ‚Äî plain text only
- [ ] No deep/filtered portal URLs ‚Äî root homepage only
- [ ] No superlatives without evidence
- [ ] All local terms explained inline on first use
- [ ] `faq` present with **8** Q&As using the standard questions from RULE 9 (city-specific answers)
- [ ] `weather` present with 12 `months` (run `scripts/generate_city_weather.py` after adding or moving a city)
- [ ] No Thailand-only jargon (TM30, Thai 90-day site, Baht rents in Tokyo, etc.) unless `countrySlug` is `thailand`
- [ ] JSON is valid (run `python3 -c "import json; json.load(open('data/cities.json'))"`)
